/HN/PR

God, grant me the ability to be alone;/PR

may it be my custom to go outdoors each day/PR

among the trees and grass,/PR

among all growing things,/PR

and there may I be alone,/PR

and enter into prayer,/PR

to talk with the One to whom I belong./PR

May I express there everything in my heart,/PR

and may all the foliage of the field/PR

(all grasses, trees and plants)/PR

may they all awake at my coming,/PR

to send the powers of their life/PR

into the words of my prayer/PR

so that my prayer and speech/PR

are made whole/PR

through the life and spirit of all growing things,/PR

which are made as one/PR

by their transcendent/PR

Source./PR

Attributed to Nah/±man of Bratzlav (translated by Shamai Kanter)/XX/PR

