/HN/PR

/PR

My thoughts awaken me to see you;/PR

They show me in my heartòs eye your deeds;/PR

They teach me to tell your wonders,/PR


"When I behold your heavens,/PR


The work your fingers made."/PR

/PR

Around its course the disk of heaven walks,/PR

A potteròs wheel enwhirling the world;/PR

It has no lips, and yet it tells your glory/PR

To earth, unmoved within its orbit,/PR


Suspended in the void,/PR


By cords of your love stayed./PI/PR

/PR

/PR

/PR

/PG764/XX/PR

Thither the sun yearns, and there burns,/PR

And of its light some to the moon lends./PR

While heavenòs sphere is spread out like a tent,/PR

With stars blooming on it, a garden,/PR


Proclaiming how profound/PR


The plans that you have laid./PR

Moses ibn Ezra (translated by Raymond Sheindlin [adapted])/XX/PR

