/HN/PR

With the ink of its showers and rains,/PR

with the quill of its lightning,/PR

with the hand of its clouds,/PR

winter wrote a letter upon the garden,/PR

in purple and blue./PR

No artist could ever conceive the like of that./PR

And this is why the earth, grown jealous of the sky,/PR

embroidered stars in the folds of the flower-beds./PR

Solomon ibn Gabirol (translated by T. Carmi)/XX/PR

